name: IPhone 14 Pro
description: The iPhone 14 Pro Max is one of the 16th generation iPhones of Apple's smartphone announced on September 7, 2022. It introduces a new 6.7-inch OLED display with a dynamic punch-out for the FaceID sensor and front camera as well as a dynamic refresh rate of 120 Hz to 1 Hz for the Always on Display.

name: IPhone 14
description: The iPhone 14 is one of the 16th generation iPhones of Apple's smartphone announced on September 7, 2022. It replaces the iPhone Mini by offering a new format for Apple's non-pro range with a 6 .7 inches with a frequency of 60 Hz.

name: IPhone 13
description: The iPhone 13, announced on September 14, 2021, is the top model of the 15th iteration of Apple's smartphone. It is equipped with a 6.1-inch 120 Hz OLED screen, an Apple A15 Bionic SoC compatible with 5G (NR & Sub-6) and a triple 12 + 12 + 12 megapixel photo sensor (wide-angle , telephoto and ultra wide-angle) with OIS.

name: IPhone 12
description: The iPhone 12 is the main model of the 14th generation of Apple smartphones announced on October 13, 2020. It is equipped with a 6.1-inch OLED HDR 60 Hz screen, a dual photo sensor with ultra large- angle and an Apple A14 Bionic SoC compatible with 5G (sub-6 GHz).

name: The iPhone SE 5G
description: The iPhone SE 5G (2022) is a smartphone announced by Apple on March 8, 2022. The third iteration of the iPhone SE lineup, it maintains a classic iPhone appearance with a 4.7-inch screen and Touch ID sensor. It integrates an Apple A15 SoC also present on the iPhone 13.

name: Samsung Galaxy S23 Ultra
description: The Samsung Galaxy S23 Ultra is the big brother of the S23 range, announced on February 1, 2023. It is equipped with a Qualcomm Snapdragon 8 Gen2 SoC supported by 8 or 12 GB of LDDR5 RAM and 216, 512 GB or 1 TB of storage

name: Samsung Galaxy S23
description: The Samsung Galaxy S23 is the successor to the Samsung Galaxy S22, announced on February 1, 2023. It is equipped with a Qualcomm Snapdragon 8 Gen2 SoC backed by 8GB of LDDR5 RAM and 128 or 256GB of storage.

name: Samsung Galaxy S22 Ultra
description: The Samsung Galaxy S22 Ultra is one of 3 smartphones in the Galaxy S22 range announced on February 9, 2022. It is equipped with an Exynos 2200 SoC backed by 8 or 12 GB of RAM and 128, 256 or 512 GB of storage.

name: Samsung Galaxy S22
description: The Samsung Galaxy S22 is one of 3 smartphones in the Galaxy S22 range announced on February 9, 2022. It is equipped with an Exynos 2200 SoC backed by 8 GB of RAM and 128 or 256 GB of storage.

name: Samsung Galaxy Z Flip 4
description: The Samsung Galaxy Z Flip 4 is the Korean company's compact folding model announced in August 2022. It features a 6.7-inch AMOLED 120 Hz adaptive display and a 1.9-inch secondary screen, a dual 12-megapixel ultra-wide-angle photo sensor and a 10-megapixel front sensor.

name: Oppo Find N2 Flip
description: The Oppo Find N2 Flip is a folding smartphone. It is positioned as a direct competitor to the Samsung Galaxy Z Flip. It has a 6.8-inch AMOLED screen with a refresh rate of 120 Hz and a small 3.26-inch external display, also AMOLED. A Mediatek SoC is included: the Dimensity 9000+, coupled with up to 16 GB of RAM and 512 GB of storage.

name: Oppo Find X5 Pro
description: Announced in February 2022, the Oppo Find X5 Pro, the more high-end model of the "Oppo Find X5" family, presents itself as an ultra-premium smartphone with a 6.7-inch WQHD+ AMOLED LTPO screen refreshed at 120 Hz, powered by a Qualcomm Snapdragon 8 Gen1 SoC, coupled with 12 GB of RAM and 256 GB of storage

name: Oppo Reno 10 Pro
description: The Oppo Reno 10 Pro, upgraded from the standard version of the "Oppo Reno 10" family, differs from its little brother by its SoC (Dimensity 8200), a higher intensity fast charge (100 W) and its photo sensor. 50-megapixel main camera with optical stabilization.

name: Oppo Find X3 Pro
description: The Oppo Find X3 Pro is the highest-end version of the Find X3 series announced in March 2021. This model comes with an AMOLED QHD+ display and an adaptive 120Hz refresh rate. It is equipped with a Qualcomm Snapdragon 888 SoC coupled with 12 GB of RAM and 256 GB of storage.
